summary: 50 days of Andi Mack
body:
50 days of Andi Mack

Season 2 Episode 6: I Wanna Hold Your Wristband

  • I love this episode! I think it’s so cool that they did an episode with such a deep and important message in a kids show
  • “I am seven years away from retirement, just do the work” 100% me if I was a teacher
  • How did Cyrus fail a connect the dots puzzle???
  • I love that little A League of Their Own reference when the gym teacher said “There’s no crying in dodgeball”
  • Dodgeball Cyrus is very disturbing. Make it stop please
  • Docious atrocious… This phrase is so bad that it’s actually good
  • That fight scene with the cookies was literally so dramatic especially Gus. I’m ashamed to say this but it reminds me if the food fight scene in the Bratz movie
  • PRIDE POSTER!!!
  • I love Dr Metcalf so much! He is seriously one of the coolest characters on the show
  • Andi called Jazz boring? We need to talk

summary: You know I'm so glad 314 and 15 are airing on the same day cause I don't think I could handle waiting another week to see my sad...
question: You know I'm so glad 314 and 15 are airing on the same day cause I don't think I could handle waiting another week to see my sad boys TJ and Cyrus give each other hurt puppy eyes.
answer: I’m just glad because that means we are starting the end of the series with all of the kids included, and ending the series with all of the kids included. Like the fact that Amber, Marty, TJ, and K*ra will all be in the June 21 episodes and the finale in July just makes me happy idk. I guess because the familial bond that the cast has makes me so happy, so knowing they’ll all play a part from start to finish makes it feel special if that makes sense.

summary: Here's the thing about the word "disappointed" that hurts so much about the 3x15 description. Disappointed means the worse of...
body:
Here’s the thing about the word “disappointed” that hurts so much about the 3x15 description. Disappointed means the worse of the worse. Not mad. Not infuriated. Not moping about. Disappointed. Cyrus being disappointed in TJ means he expected more from TJ Kippen. Cyrus thought TJ was different. Cyrus thought TJ was better than bailing on him for costume day (when it was his idea to begin). Cyrus being disappointed by TJ’s friendship means he thought TJ was better than hanging out with someone as problematic as Kira. But TJ was not better. TJ Kippen failed to fulfill any of Cyrus’ expectations and-

Excuse me, my eyes are sweating.
